Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.78,0:00:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up in the South \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.78,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,during the time of segregation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.11,0:00:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—blacks and whites—\Nwe couldn’t mix. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.99,0:00:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only that, they had signs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.41,0:00:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep you knowing \Nwhere you were supposed to go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.54,0:00:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t understand \Nwhy we couldn’t get along.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifty cents.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.46,0:00:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.38,0:00:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Sir.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.51,0:00:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma, he’s just a boy. \NWhy are you saying “Sir”?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.89,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet. \NI want you to know your place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.52,0:00:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her after we got back on the truck: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.56,0:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“You know what? \NI’ll never hold my head down!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.36,0:00:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother \Nknew I had a love for the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I would \Nalways read the Bible as a kid. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.03,0:00:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn’t understand it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.00,0:01:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to pray, \N“What makes us so different?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.04,0:01:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \N“Why can’t we live together?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.59,0:01:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a group, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.22,0:01:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and this group was like \Nwhat I really wanted to be in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.18,0:01:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They were about politics. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.68,0:01:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, “We’re fighting injustice.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they said \Nthat word “injustice,” it was like, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.98,0:01:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Yeah, this is what I want to be in, right?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.57,0:01:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘To be part of something that can change \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.86,0:01:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and make people united, right?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.28,0:01:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my goal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.53,0:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We started protesting about police brutality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.28,0:01:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think that’s what a lot of people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.87,0:01:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, \Nwere focusing on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.37,0:01:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked some of the things \Nthat they were doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.21,0:01:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but they trained us every, \Nevery day in military training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned how to use weapons \Nand stuff like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I’m thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.34,0:01:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This is not what I want to be in. \NThis is not what I joined.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.60,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started going back to God again\N—to reading the Bible—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.81,0:02:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was like \NI’m not changing anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.48,0:02:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible that I was reading \Nwas the King James Version. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.56,0:02:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was reading it, reading it, reading it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.73,0:02:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn’t understand it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Jamaica, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.90,0:02:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we saw this Bible, \Nthe New World Translation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.87,0:02:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I started reading it, \Nand it made so much sense! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could understand it, \Nand it wasn’t “thee” and “thou.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.50,0:02:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like, ‘Wow!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like, \N‘This is the one I want to get.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, two women knocked on the door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know they were Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.72,0:02:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All I could see was that Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, \N“Where did you get that Bible from?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.10,0:02:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said, \N“OK, we’ll bring you one.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.35,0:02:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did. \NSo they brought me the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t know I was going to have \Na Bible study that came along with it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I went \Nto a convention of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like ten thousand people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.28,0:02:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went in there and I saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.74,0:02:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all these different faces \Nand different colors, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:02:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like Jehovah showing me: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, Rafika, remember you were asking me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.29,0:03:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“about all different people \Ngetting together and being one? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I’m not partial; \Nthey do get along; we are unified.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.34,0:03:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just made me feel so good inside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.59,0:03:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.30,0:03:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the organization \Nthat I want to be in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just see people as people, you know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can preach \Nand be friends with anybody. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I know \Nwhat the Bible really teaches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a wonderful life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because I know \Nthat only God and his government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can bring about peace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.78,0:03:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like how Jehovah \Nunified everybody, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.95,0:03:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody \Nto be unified\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.54,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and come to know Jehovah, \Njust like I know him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:04:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered my prayer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.90,0:00:10.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは人種隔離の時代に\Nアメリカ南部で育ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:14.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,黒人と白人は隔離されていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.79,0:00:20.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「白人専用」とか「非白人専用」という\N看板があったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.04,0:00:24.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして仲良くできないんだろうと\N思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.67,0:00:25.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,50セント\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.75,0:00:27.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい だんな様\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.80,0:00:29.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.68,0:00:33.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,おばあちゃん 子どもなのに\Nどうして「だんな様」って呼ぶの？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.05,0:00:37.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,お黙りなさい\N白人はわたしたちより上なのよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.47,0:00:40.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラックに戻ってから祖母に言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.19,0:00:44.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,「黒人だからって\N下だとは思わないわ！」\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは聖書が大好きで\Nいつも読んでいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも意味はよく分かりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.87,0:00:59.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく こう祈りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.87,0:01:01.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人はみんな同じじゃないんですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.96,0:01:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして一緒に暮らせないんですか？」\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.30,0:01:11.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある組織にかかわるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.51,0:01:15.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,その組織がすごく気に入ったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.01,0:01:20.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,政治的な組織で\N「不公正を正す」と言っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.43,0:01:22.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを聞いて思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.69,0:01:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「その通りよ！社会を変えて\Nみんな一致しなきゃ！」\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.40,0:01:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それこそ わたしの目指すものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.78,0:01:38.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,警察の野蛮な行動に抗議しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.12,0:01:42.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,その当時\N盛んに議論されていた問題でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,組織の活動に\N賛同できた点もありましたが\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:50.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎日やらされた軍事訓練には\N参加したくありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.21,0:01:53.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,武器の使い方などを\N練習させられたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.63,0:01:57.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「わたしが求めているのは\Nこんなんじゃない」と思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:01.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 以前のように\N聖書を読むことにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:05.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,その組織にいても\N何も変えられないと分かったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:08.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェームズ王欽定訳聖書を読みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:12.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,何度も読みましたが意味が分かりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.65,0:02:16.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジャマイカに行った時\N初めて「新世界訳聖書」を見ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.91,0:02:19.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみると 意味が分かるんです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:22.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「汝は」なんて出てきません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:26.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,感動して「こういう聖書が\N欲しい！」と思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.71,0:02:29.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 二人の女性が訪問してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.84,0:02:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,真っ先に目に入ったのは\Nその人たちの持っていた聖書でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.09,0:02:38.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが「その聖書\Nどこで手に入るんですか？」と聞くと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:40.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「1冊お持ちします」と言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.51,0:02:43.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでやっと「新世界訳」が\N手に入ったんですが\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:47.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究も一緒に付いてくるって\N知りませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.44,0:02:50.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めてエホバの証人の大会に出席した時\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:53.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席者は1万人くらいだったと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:57.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな顔かたち\N肌の色の人たちがいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.70,0:03:00.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,まるでエホバが\Nこうおっしゃったようでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:06.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ラフィカ いろんな人種の人たちが\N一つになれるようにと祈っていたね？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:11.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご覧 わたしは不公平な神ではないんだよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.55,0:03:14.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にすがすがしい気持ちになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそ わたしが\N求めていた組織でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.93,0:03:22.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな同じ人間です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.26,0:03:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれにでも伝道して友達になれるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:30.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が実際に教えているのは\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.90,0:03:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と神の王国だけが\N世界を平和にできるということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを知って 人生が豊かになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.78,0:03:43.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが人を一致させます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:48.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんながエホバを知って\N一致するよう願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:04:07.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはわたしの祈りに\N答えてくださいました\N
